Study

DaemonSet: one pod per node (logging, monitoring, CNI).
Job: run to completion. completions, parallelism, backoffLimit.
CronJob: schedule jobs via cron expression. concurrencyPolicy: Allow|Forbid|Replace.
Hands-On

# DaemonSet — fluent-bit or simple busybox
kubectl apply -f fluentbit-ds.yaml
kubectl get ds -A

# Job
kubectl create job pi --image=perl -- perl -Mbignum=bpi -wle 'print bpi(2000)'
kubectl logs job/pi

# CronJob
kubectl create cronjob hello --image=busybox --schedule="*/1 * * * *" -- echo Hello
kubectl get cronjob,jobs

